{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, data usage has been approved by relevant ethics committees, ensuring compliance with ethical standards and privacy protection requirements.",
    "There are plenty of works that adopt the clinical agent to solve specific clinical scenarios.",
    "One type of work focuses on medical knowledge argument with retrieval from the knowledge base.",
    "For example, BioKGBench (Lin et al., 2024) proposes a knowledge graph-based evaluation benchmark to mitigate hallucination issues by testing biomedical agents on scientific claim verification and their ability to interact with structured knowledge graphs.",
    "MedRAG (Xiong et al., 2024) presents a retrievalaugmented generation (RAG) benchmark designed to evaluate medical question-answering systems, focusing on reducing hallucinations and enhancing factual accuracy by incorporating external knowledge retrieval."
  ]
}